{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"65937484-3ad4-4d95-a20d-f7e8a2fe54df","content":"MSTest v3 dropped support for `.testsettings` — you need a `.runsettings` file instead.\n\nI created **`local.runsettings`** that migrates your two settings:\n\n| `.testsettings` setting | `.runsettings` equivalent |\n|---|---|\n| `useLoadContext=\"true\"` (assembly resolution) | `<DeploymentEnabled>false</DeploymentEnabled>` — loads from the test directory directly |\n| `TestTimeout = 30000` | `<TestTimeout>30000</TestTimeout>` |\n\n**To use it**, either:\n- Run: `dotnet test --settings local.runsettings`\n- Or add `<RunSettingsFilePath>$(MSBuildProjectDirectory)\\local.runsettings</RunSettingsFilePath>` to a `<PropertyGroup>` in your `.csproj` to make it automatic.\n\nYou can safely delete `local.testsettings` once confirmed.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"da9e812d-5f21-4029-9bb4-fd53e24e3cdd","outputTokens":228},"id":"cf60f119-9d94-43bc-8b52-7dd309eecb7a","timestamp":"2026-04-03T01:15:46.482Z","parentId":"2a45ba0f-cc08-4451-adbe-c047187d8a30"}
